          <li><strong>5. Reference Real Photography:</strong> Invoke lenses/styles: "shot on Canon EOS R5, 50mm f/1.8 lens, shallow depth of field" or "cinematic Studio Ghibli anime with hand-drawn textures." Boosts realism 3x for fashion headshots.</li>
          <li><strong>6. Iterative Refinement Chain:</strong> After generation, critique specifically: "Make Hindi text bolder and more legible, increase saturation on saffron robes by 20%, swap background to authentic Bihar river ghat." Maintains consistency across 10-image series.</li>
          <li><strong>7. Cultural Precision:</strong> For India-specific work: "authentic Bihar Chhath Puja elements including bamboo soops, thekua sweets, mustard oil lamps, diverse skin tones, traditional cotton sarees." Eliminates Western bias.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Pro Tip: Use Plus tier's "thinking mode" for complex scenes—it self-corrects composition before rendering. These techniques deliver 87% photorealism, powering India's creator economy with zero-designer costs.</p>
